cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.DS

The paper proposes a novel algorithm for training neural networks via stochastic gradient descent and variants thereof. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the theoretical properties of the algorithm, which suggests that it could be relevant to the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) category. Additionally, the paper applies the algorithm to image classification tasks, which could place it in the cs.CV (Computer Vision) category. The paper also discusses the numerical implementation of the algorithm, which could be relevant to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) category. Finally, the paper could be relevant to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) category, given that it proposes a new algorithm for training neural networks.
